Ext.data.JsonP['Data-Driven_Tests']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Data-Driven Tests</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-43298701\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Data-Driven Tests</h1>\n    <p>    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-warning aui-message problem shadowed information-macro\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Enterprise Subscription Required!</div>\n            <p>This AMPLIFY(<sup class=\" \">TM</sup>) Appcelerator Services feature requires an Enterprise Subscription.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>    </p>\n    <p>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-Introduction\">Introduction</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreateaData-DrivenTest\">Create a Data-Driven Test</a>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreatetheSeedData\">Create the Seed Data</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreateaTestClip\">Create a Test Clip</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-ModifytheTestCliptoUsetheSeedData\">Modify the Test Clip to Use the Seed Data</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreateaTestCompositiontoLoopoverSeedData\">Create a Test Composition to Loop over Seed Data</a>    </p>\n</li></ul></li></ul>    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-Introduction\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Introduction</span></h2>\n    <p>This page describes how to use static or dynamic data sets to input values in to an application and validate values returned by the application.  These directions assume you are familiar with Appcelerator Test, and have already registered your device(s) and know how to create a test clip.  For information on getting started with Appcelerator Test, see <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Getting_started_with_Test\">Getting started with Test</a>.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreateaData-DrivenTest\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Create a Data-Driven Test</span></h2>\n    <p>The following steps outline how to create a data-driven test.    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Log in to the <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"https://platform.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Appcelerator Dashboard</a>, select an application to test, and click on the <strong class=\" \">Test</strong> <strong class=\" \"> </strong>tab.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Create seed data with input values and validation values.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Create a test clip that receives input data (manually) and presents the validation data on screen, for example, entering a stock symbol and checking the company name.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Modify the clip so that the input is retrieved from the seed data and to validate data from the seed data.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Create a composition that loops over the seed data set.    </p>\n</li></ol>    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreatetheSeedData\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Create the Seed Data</span></h3>\n    <p>You need to create seed data that contains input values and corresponding output values to validate your application.  You can either manually create the data set, or import data from a local or remote CSV file.  If you want to import data from a remote source, skip to the &quot;Create a Test Clip&quot; section.    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In the Appcelerator Test Dashboard, in the <strong class=\" \">Central</strong> tab, select the <strong class=\" \">New</strong> button     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/37523016/NewButton.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/37523016/NewButton.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-external-resource\">\n (click on the down arrow), then   <strong class=\" \">New Seed Data</strong> . The  <strong class=\" \">Seed Data Editor</strong>   tab opens.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Seed Data Editor</strong> tab, enter a name and optionally a description for your data set.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>If you want to encrypt your data, check <strong class=\" \">The data should be encrypted</strong> checkbox and enter a password in the <strong class=\" \">key</strong> textbox.  When using this option, you will be prompted for the password when editing your seed data and running your test clip.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Choose to either import a CSV file or manually enter your data:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>To import a CSV file, click the <strong class=\" \">Import a CSV file</strong> radio button, then click <strong class=\" \">Choose file</strong> to select a CSV file to import.<br>If the first row contains column headings, check the  <strong class=\" \">First row contains the column names</strong>  checkbox.    </br></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>To manually enter your data, click <strong class=\" \">Create a Seed Data Object</strong>.    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the right green arrow button to proceed to the next step.    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>If you chose to import data, your data will be populated.  You can optionally edit the values.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>If you chose to manually enter your data, create your data columns and enter your data values.    </p>\n</li></ul></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Once done, click <strong class=\" \">Finish</strong>.    </p>\n</li></ol>    <p>If you need to edit your seed data again, in the <strong class=\" \">Central </strong>tab, click <strong class=\" \">Seed Data</strong> in the left navigation pane, which lists all of your data sets in the right pane.  Double-click the entry you want to edit to open the data with the <strong class=\" \">Seed Data Editor</strong>.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreateaTestClip\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Create a Test Clip</span></h3>\n    <p>First, create a basic test clip where you input a data value in to the application then receive a result.  To create a basic test case, see <a class=\"document-link unresolved\" href=\"#!/guide/Data-Driven_Tests-section-src-43298701\">Test: Create a Test Clip</a>.  Be sure to create a validation step to check the value of the result.    </p>\n    <p>For example, in this simple test, a user enters a value in a textfield and clicks a button to submit it, then the application performs a calculation and displays a result.    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/SampleApp.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/SampleApp.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        </img></p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                    <div class=\"title\">Resources/app.js</div>\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\" data-title=\"Resources/app.js\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">function calcFib(val) {  </code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    </code><code class=\"keyword\">if</code><code class=\"plain\"> (val == </code><code class=\"value\">0</code><code class=\"plain\"> || val == </code><code class=\"value\">1</code><code class=\"plain\">){</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    \t</code><code class=\"keyword\">return</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"value\">1</code><code class=\"plain\">;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    }</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    </code><code class=\"keyword\">else</code><code class=\"plain\"> {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    \t</code><code class=\"keyword\">return</code><code class=\"plain\"> calcFib(val - </code><code class=\"value\">1</code><code class=\"plain\">) + calcFib(val - </code><code class=\"value\">2</code><code class=\"plain\">);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">    }</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">}</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var intRegex = /^\\d+$/;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">function submitValue(){</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tvar val = textField.value;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\t</code><code class=\"keyword\">if</code><code class=\"plain\">(val &amp;&amp; intRegex.test(val)) {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\t\tlabel2.text = calcFib(val);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\t\twin2.open();</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\t\twin1.close();</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\t\ttextField.value = </code><code class=\"string\">&quot;&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\">;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\t}</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">}</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\">&#xA0;</div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var win2 = Ti.UI.createWindow({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tbackgroundColor: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;white&apos;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">});</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var label2 = Ti.UI.createLabel({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tfont: {fontSize: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;24dp&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">, fontWeight: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;bold&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">}</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">});</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">win2.add(label2);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\">&#xA0;</div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var win1 = Ti.UI.createWindow({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tbackgroundColor: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;white&apos;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">});</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var label1 = Ti.UI.createLabel({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\ttop: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;10dp&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tfont: {fontSize: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;14dp&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">},</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\ttext: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;Enter a positive integer:&apos;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">});</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var textField = Ti.UI.createTextField({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\twidth: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;100dp&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\theight: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;25dp&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tborderWidth: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;1&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\ttop: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;50dp&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\tkeyboardType: Ti.UI.KEYBOARD_NUMBER_PAD</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">});</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">var button = Ti.UI.createButton({</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\ttitle: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;Calculate&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">,</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">\ttop: </code><code class=\"string\">&apos;100dp&apos;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">});</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">button.addEventListener(</code><code class=\"string\">&apos;click&apos;</code><code class=\"plain\">, submitValue)</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">win1.add(label1);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">win1.add(textField);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">win1.add(button);</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">win1.open();</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>    </p>\n    <p>To create the test clip for this example, once you have connected your device and started recording:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In the application, click the textfield.  A tap action appears in the test clip.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>You can optionally edit the action to wait for the textfield to appear before proceeding to enter data.    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>When the action is populated, a configuration box appears.  Click on the Wait icon (set of hour glasses).    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Under the <strong class=\" \">Waits before the action </strong>section, click the Add icon (green plus sign) to create a new pre-action wait.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Command</strong> drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">waitForElementPresent</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Next to the <strong class=\" \">Locator</strong> textfield, click the Locator Tool icon     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/LocatorIcon.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/LocatorIcon.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n.  A blue border appears around your application.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the application, click the textfield.  A textbox appears with several labels.  Click the blue up arrow in the top-right corner of the box.  The <strong class=\" \">Locator</strong> textfield populates with a value similar to <strong class=\" \">classname=UIFieldEditor </strong>or <strong class=\" \">classname=TiTextField</strong>.  You are done creating the pre-action wait condition.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/WaitForPreAction.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/WaitForPreAction.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n    </img></li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the application, enter a value in the textfield, then click the <strong class=\" \">Calculate </strong>button.  The application opens a resulting value in a new window, and a type and tap action appear in the test clip.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Edit the action to wait for a post-action condition and to check for a value.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>To create a post-action wait condition:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>When the tap action is populated, a configuration box appears.  Click on the Wait icon (set of hour glasses).    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Under the <strong class=\" \">Waits after the action </strong>section, click the Add icon (green plus sign) to create a new post-action wait.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Command</strong> drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">waitForElementPresent</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Next to the <strong class=\" \">Locator</strong> textfield, click the Locator Tool icon     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/LocatorIcon.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/LocatorIcon.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n.  A blue border appears around your application.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the application, click the result label.  A textbox appears with several labels.  Click the blue up arrow in the top-right corner of the box.  The <strong class=\" \">Locator</strong> textfield populates with a value similar to <strong class=\" \">classname=UILabel</strong>.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/WaitForPostAction.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/WaitForPostAction.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n    </img></li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>To create a validation condition:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In the configuration box, click on the Validations icon (green checkmark).    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the Add icon (green plus sign) to create a new validate condition.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Command</strong> drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">waitForElementPropertyValue</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Next to the <strong class=\" \">Locator</strong> textfield, click the Locator Tool icon     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/LocatorIcon.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/LocatorIcon.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n.  A blue border appears around your application.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the application, click the result label.  A textbox appears with several labels.  Click the blue up arrow in the top-right corner of the box.  The <strong class=\" \">Locator</strong> textfield populates with a value similar to <strong class=\" \">classname=UILabel</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Property </strong>textfield, enter <strong class=\" \">text</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the textfield with <strong class=\" \">Exact Match </strong>selected in the drop-down box, enter the value of the result.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/ValidationAction.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/ValidationAction.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n    </img></li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>To test that the clip has been set up to receive manually entered data and to check the value of the result.  Run the test clip in a test composition to verify it works before proceeding to the next step.    </p>\n</li></ol>    <p>    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-info aui-message hint shadowed information-macro\">\n            <p>The previous procedure is only a simple example of using pre-action wait conditions, post-action wait conditions and validation condition.  There are many different commands you can use for these actions.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-ModifytheTestCliptoUsetheSeedData\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Modify the Test Clip to Use the Seed Data</span></h3>\n    <p>Next, modify the test clip to use the seed data.  You need to add the seed data as a custom property of the test clip and change the input value and result value to use the seed data.    </p>\n    <p>First, add the seed data to the test clip:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>If your test clip is not already opened in the <strong class=\" \">Clip Editor</strong> tab, in the <strong class=\" \">Central</strong> tab, click <strong class=\" \">Clips </strong>in the left navigation pane, which lists all of your test clips.  Double-click the clip you want to edit to open it in the <strong class=\" \">Clip Editor</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the  <strong class=\" \">Properties</strong>  tab .    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Select <strong class=\" \">Clip Custom Properties</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the Add icon (green plus sign) to create a new custom property.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>If you desire, change the name of the property.  By default, the first name is <strong class=\" \">clipProp</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>To use seed data that you either created manually or imported from a local CSV file:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Value </strong>drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">Seed Data: Repository</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Seed data object</strong> drop-down box, select the seed data object you created.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Skip to the next step pertaining to remote CSV data.    </p>\n</li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>To use seed data from a remote CSV file:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Value </strong>drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">Seed Data: Repository</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">URL </strong>textfield, enter the URL of where the data file is located.  Check the <strong class=\" \">Column names are in the first row</strong> checkbox if the first row of the file are the column headings.    </p>\n</li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Scroll to the bottom of the custom properties to the <strong class=\" \">Data</strong> section.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Row traversal type</strong> drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">Sequential</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">EOF action</strong> drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">Stop Track and Drain</strong>, which will try to run the track one last time when it reaches the end of the seed data, but returns a <strong class=\" \">Completed Result</strong> when the composition finishes.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/ClipProperty.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/ClipProperty.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        <p>    </p>\n</img></li></ol>    <p>Next, use the seed data to input data in to the application:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Double-click the action where the test clip enters the input value.  This should be a &quot;type&quot; action.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Make sure <strong class=\" \">Inputs </strong>is selected in the lower pane.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Erase the input value in the <strong class=\" \">Text</strong> textfield and click the ISSE Editor icon     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/IsseIcon.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/IsseIcon.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n next to it to open the ISSE editor.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Make sure <strong class=\" \">Property</strong> is selected in the top row and <strong class=\" \">Custom</strong> is selected in right section of the editor.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the right section of the editor, select the property with your seed data and in the <strong class=\" \">Modifier(s)</strong> drop-down box, select the column you want to use.  If the column has a title, this is the name of the column (may appear as random characters for encrypted data).  If the column is not titled, you need to select the column number.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">OK </strong>button. The textfield now contains a property.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/IsseEditor.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/IsseEditor.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        <p>    </p>\n</img></li></ol>    <p>Finally, use the seed data to validate the result from the application:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Double-click the action where the test clip validates the result value.  In the simple example, this is in the last &quot;tap&quot; action.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Select <strong class=\" \">Validations </strong>in the lower pane.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Erase the result value in the textfield and click the ISSE Editor icon     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/IsseIcon.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/IsseIcon.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n next to it to open the ISSE editor.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Make sure <strong class=\" \">Property</strong> is selected in the top row and <strong class=\" \">Custom</strong> is selected in right section of the editor.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the right section of the editor, select the property with your seed data and in the <strong class=\" \">Modifier(s)</strong> drop-down box, select the column you want to use.  If the column has a title, this is the name of the column (may appear as random characters for encrypted data).  If the column is not titled, you need to select the column number.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">OK </strong>button.  The textfield now contains a property.    </p>\n</li></ol>    <p>To verify the test clip is using seed data correctly, run the test clip in a test composition.  The test composition runs the test clip once with the first row of the seed data.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-43298701_Data-DrivenTests-CreateaTestCompositiontoLoopoverSeedData\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Create a Test Composition to Loop over Seed Data</span></h3>\n    <p>Finally, you need to create a test composition that loops over the test clip.  You need to modify the band and track properties before adding the test clip.  Do not use the <strong class=\" \">Open in Test Composition</strong> or <strong class=\" \">Play in Test Composition</strong> options from the Test Clip Editor.  You cannot edit the band properties once the test clip has been added.    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Central</strong> tab, select the <strong class=\" \">New</strong> button     <img src=\"images/download/attachments/37523016/NewButton.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/37523016/NewButton.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-external-resource\">\n (click on the down arrow), then   <strong class=\" \">New Test Composition</strong> . The <strong class=\" \">Test Composition</strong>  <strong class=\" \"> Editor</strong>   tab opens.    </img></p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Right-click on the <strong class=\" \">Sequenced Band</strong> label and select <strong class=\" \">Change timing type</strong>.  This changes the band from sequenced to timed, which allows the track to be looped.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/BandTiming.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/BandTiming.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n        <p>    </p>\n</img></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">Properties</strong> tab in the lower pane.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Check the <strong class=\" \">Enable Repeat</strong> checkbox.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Repeat Method</strong> drop-down box, select <strong class=\" \">Infinite</strong>, which loops over the seed data until the EOF event.    </p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/TrackProperties.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/43298701/TrackProperties.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image\">\n    </img></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the <strong class=\" \">Composition Build</strong> tab in the lower pane.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Locate and drag the test clip to the test track or band to add it to the test composition.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click the Play icon to start the test.    </p>\n</li></ol>    <p>The editor switches to the <strong class=\" \">Play</strong> tab.  The test clip executes repeatedly until the seed data runs out.    </p>\n    <p>    </p>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=43298701\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Data-Driven Tests"});